Differential Protein Expression Analysis

Vishnu Ramasubramanian

2025-02-02

1 Introduction

This document outlines the workflow for differential enrichment analysis of Mass Spectrometer (MS) proteomics data using the DEP package in R. Two comparisons are analyzed:

  1. MO vs.TNB
  2. Bert vs.TN (CRISPR)

2 Objective

The objective of this analysis is to compare the protein expression profile ofconventionally-bred triple-mutant lines_vs_recurrent parents and crispr triple-mutants_vs_bert. This analysis will help us assess crispr tech and conventionally generated mutant lines in terms of changes in the proteome landscape induced by these two different approaches to generating mutants.

5 Results

5.1 Comparative Analysis of DEP Results

5.1.1 Volcano plot for MO_vs_TNB analysis

#pVol <- plot_volcano(dep, contrast='Mutant_vs_Control', label_size=2, adjusted=TRUE, add_names=TRUE)

pVol <- plot_volcano(dep1, contrast='Mutant_vs_Control', label_size=2, adjusted=TRUE, add_names=TRUE)

# Extract data from the plot object
volcano_data <- pVol$data

# Add a new column for DE categories based on x and significance
volcano_data$DE <- with(volcano_data, 
                        ifelse(significant & x > 0, "Up", 
                               ifelse(significant & x < 0, "Down", "NS"))
)

# Convert DE column to a factor for consistent plotting
volcano_data$DE <- factor(volcano_data$DE, levels = c("Up", "Down", "NS"))

# Create the volcano plot with new DE column
pVol <- ggplot(volcano_data, aes(x = x, y = y, color = DE)) +
  geom_point(size = 3) +
  scale_color_manual(
    values = c(
      "Up" = "red",         # Upregulated proteins
      "Down" = "blue",      # Downregulated proteins
      "NS" = "gray"         # Non-significant proteins
    )
  ) +
  geom_text_repel(
    aes(label = ifelse(DE != "NS", name, "")), # Label significant points (Up or Down)
    max.overlaps = 50,
    size = 3
  ) +
  theme_minimal() +
  labs(
    title = "Volcano Plot of DEP for MO_vs_TNB",
    x = "Log2 Fold Change",
    y = "-Log10 Adjusted P-value",
    color = "Expression"
  )

# Display the volcano plot
print(pVol)

# Save the customized plot

ggsave("prtnquant-volcanoplot_V2_MO_vs_TNB.png", plot = pVol, width = 10, height = 8)

6 Conclusion

The proteins Glyma.02G012600, Glyma.08G341500, and Glyma.08G116300, which are the target proteins in the triple null mutant and CRISPR mutant lines, are significantly down-regulated in both the comparisons with the respective controls. Further analysis of other differentially expressed proteins will be performed as part of future studies.
